{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17656896","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17656896"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T22:21:05+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T22:21:05+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18913"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18913","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18913"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.06,0.01,0.88,0,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11646"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96060"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11646","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11646"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18913"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"78792"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"928"},{"type":"tags","id":"1804"},{"type":"tags","id":"5351"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11349"},{"type":"tags","id":"11357"},{"type":"tags","id":"11358"},{"type":"tags","id":"11359"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27394"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27395"},{"type":"contributions","id":"32901"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96060","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/96060"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA medical student is preparing for their clinical placement at a healthcare centre that serves a significant Indigenous population. The student wants to ensure they provide culturally safe care.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes an appropriate approach to providing culturally safe care for Indigenous patients?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Referring all Indigenous patients to Indigenous healthcare workers","Making decisions for patients to ensure best medical outcomes","Recognising personal biases and respecting Indigenous perspectives on health","Assuming all Indigenous patients prefer traditional healing methods","Treating all patients identically regardless of cultural background"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct approach involves \u003Cstrong\u003Erecognising personal biases and respecting Indigenous perspectives on health\u003C/strong\u003E. Cultural safety requires healthcare providers to examine their own cultural assumptions while acknowledging and respecting Indigenous ways of understanding health and wellbeing. This includes recognising that Indigenous concepts of health are holistic, encompassing physical, spiritual, cultural, emotional, and social dimensions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect approaches are problematic because:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAssuming all Indigenous patients prefer traditional healing methods\u003C/strong\u003E stereotypes Indigenous people and fails to recognise individual preferences and diversity within Indigenous communities\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMaking decisions for patients to ensure best medical outcomes\u003C/strong\u003E - This paternalistic approach disempowers patients and fails to respect their autonomy\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETreating all patients identically regardless of cultural background\u003C/strong\u003E ignores important cultural differences and historical contexts that impact healthcare experiences and outcomes\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReferring all Indigenous patients to Indigenous healthcare workers\u003C/strong\u003E - While Indigenous healthcare workers play a valuable role, all healthcare providers should be competent in providing culturally safe care\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECultural safety involves ongoing self-reflection, building trust, and working in partnership with Indigenous patients while acknowledging the impact of historical trauma and systemic barriers to healthcare.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Cultural safety requires healthcare providers to examine their own cultural values and biases while respecting Indigenous ways of understanding health.","Indigenous concepts of health are holistic, encompassing physical, spiritual, cultural, emotional, and social wellbeing.","Building trust with Indigenous patients requires recognition of historical trauma and ongoing systemic barriers to healthcare."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx","Curtis E, Jones R, Tipene-Leach D, Walker C, Loring B, Paine SJ, Reid P. Why cultural safety rather than cultural competency is required to achieve health equity: a literature review and recommended definition. International journal for equity in health. 2019 Dec;18:1-7."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"78792"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18913"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"78792","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/78792"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-30T20:42:45+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-03-30T20:42:46+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11646"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96060"}}},"meta":{"canDe